Also , please accept our sincere apologies if you receive multiple copies of this CFP . * * * NOTE EXTENSION OF DEADLINE TO MARCH 30 * * * Also note that selected papers on the theme topic will appear in a Special Issue of the ACM Journal MONET . DSOM '98 NINTH IFIP / IEEE INTERNATIONAL WORKSHOP ON DISTRIBUTED SYSTEMS : OPERATIONS & MANAGEMENT CALL FOR PAPERS University of Delaware Newark , Delaware , USA Oct . 26 - 28 , 1998 http : / / www . cis . udel . edu / ~ dsom 98 Sponsored by the International Federation for Information Processing ( IFIP ) Working Group 6 . 6 on Network Management for Communication Networks with technical co-sponsorship by the IEEE Communications Society Technical Committee on Network Operations and Management ( CNOM ) . WORKSHOP TOPICS OF INTEREST The scope of this workshop will be the operations and management of application software or services within a distributed system and the impact of advanced computing and network technologies on management . THEME TOPIC : MANAGEMENT OF MOBILITY The workshop has chosen "Management of Mobility" as its Theme Topic . Mobile or nomadic users may connect via a variety of different channels , 10 - 1000 M . bit local area networks , dial up modems , mobile telephones etc . Users may be connecting from different places ( office , home , hotel ) at different times or may actually be mobile in a train or car . New infrastructure and services are needed to support seamless interaction over network channels with widely varying quality of service . Intelligent filtering and caching mechanisms are needed to adjust traffic to available bandwidth . Location services are needed to track users for location aware applications or to redirect traffic to the nearest network access point . This workshop will address the issues of managing these mobile users as well as the support services and infrastructure . The workshop will provide technical sessions with adequate time for discussion on presented papers and panel sessions with invited experts to explore specific poblems and future directions . Papers are invited on the following subjects related to the Theme Topic : * Management of Mobile ( nomadic ) users or systems * Management of services to support mobility - location , caching , information filter etc . * Intelligent Agent Technologies to support mobility * Management of mobile agents * Management of Wireless Networks ( including Wireless LANs , Intranets , and Wireless ATM ) * Configuration Management for Mobile Systems * Security Management for Mobile Systems * Managing Quality of Service in Mobile Systems * Managing Multimedia and Integrated Services in Mobile Systems * Routing , Path , and Self-configuration Management in Mobile and Ad-hoc Networks * New Tools , Protocols , Architectures , etc . for Management of Mobile Computing SELECTED PAPERS FROM THE WORKSHOP ON THE THEME TOPIC WILL BE PUBLISHED IN THE ACM JOURNAL MONET ( MOBILE NETWORKING AND APPLICATIONS ) . The workshop also invites papers on a wide variety of topics related to the operations and management of distributed systems and networks . See the Workshop 's Web Page http : / / www . cis . udel . edu / ~ dsom 98 for more information on these topics . PAPER SUBMISSION : Submissions should be complete , full-length papers ( not extended abstracts ) and should not exceed 12 double-spaced pages . Electronic submission of papers is strongly encouraged via anonymous ftp in either PDF or Postscript formats . Full instructions for the electronic submissions are available on the workshop 's web page at http : / / www . cis . udel . edu / ~ dsom 98 In case you are not able to submit your paper electronically , please mail 4 copies of your paper to : Adarshpal Sethi , General and Program Chair Department of Computer & Information Sciences University of Delaware Newark , DE 19716 USA Tel : + 1 302 831 1945 Fax : + 1 302 831 8458 Email : dsom 98 @ on . aib . mh IMPORTANT DATES : March 30 , 1998 : Deadline for Papers * * NOTE NEW EXTENDED DEADLINE * * June 5 , 1998 : Notifications of acceptance mailed July 20 , 1998 : Final papers due Oct . 1 , 1998 : Deadline for advance registration Oct . 26 -
